1.title: OCD Goldilocks
1.plot: In episode 1 of "In Therapy," Dr. T. works with her young patient, OCD Goldilocks, who struggles with her neurotic desire for everything to be juuuuuuuuust right.

2.title: Wicked Stepmother
2.plot: Dr. T talks to Goldilocks's Wicked Stepmother, who faces her own issues with inflated ego, semi-maniacal mother skills, and a penchant for poisoning. Things get rough, though, when the session goes awry...

3.title: Big Bad Wolf
3.plot: Dr. T's patient The Big Bad Wolf saves the day when he helps out Dr. T, who is now trapped in her office thanks to Wicked Stepmother's spell. The session goes deep into the Wolf's eating issues, particularly when it comes to staying a vegetarian in the woods.

4.title: Therapist's Therapist
4.plot: Dr. T has an emergency house call with her own Therapist as she tries to get through her work week and break the spell cast on her by the Wicked Stepmother.

imdb.plot outline: In the original comedy web-series "In Therapy," our Therapist works with her favorite kinds of patients: slightly-crazy storybook characters. In Episode 1, she treats an OCD-afflicted Goldilocks; in Epsidoe 2, the Wicked Stepmother shows her true neurotic colors; in Episode 3, the Big Bad Wolf deals with his emotional eating issues; and in Episode 4, the Therapist seeks help from her own, much more grounded, analyst. Let the healing begin.
